                            <comment id="13488072" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Wed, 31 Oct 2012 18:39:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks. After glancing at the code I don&apos;t think this is specific to JBoss.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13488073" author="anawasthi" created="Wed, 31 Oct 2012 18:42:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think so too.  Has anyone experienced this before. I am debugging the source code and does not look like that log4J context even picks up the configuration file. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13488092" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Wed, 31 Oct 2012 18:56:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Many of the unit tests use the system property so it does get picked up. But the File object isn&apos;t being passed to the constructor so File monitoring probably isn&apos;t working. I suspect I broke this when in a prior fix.  This should have been caught by a unit test.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BTW - you have strict=&quot;true&quot; in your configuration but then you aren&apos;t using the strict syntax.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13488118" author="anawasthi" created="Wed, 31 Oct 2012 19:13:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;thanks, can you put that fix back.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13488944" author="anawasthi" created="Thu, 1 Nov 2012 19:10:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;any update on this. BTW, which constructor are you talking about. thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13488978" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Thu, 1 Nov 2012 20:01:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I checked in a fix last night but I have some more testing to do. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13489962" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Sat, 3 Nov 2012 07:45:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I added a unit test that verifies that the configuration can be located as a File and then be reconfigured. Please verify and close.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
